reviews.review_text: Connecting with Dad Wow, this is an absolutely beautiful recording. Vocals and instrumentals are really clear. This is the first one of the many shows my dad traveled from Chicago out to Red Rocks for. I remember my dad telling me about how much he pissed off my mom since he left her at home with a two year old (me) to go out to Colorado to party with is college friends. Thanks for getting me into the dead, I miss you Dad.
Red Rocks 1978 I had no idea Jerry Moore was at this concert, running a tape deck. I was familiar with his earlier recordings, especially from Indy in 1976  >  R.I.P. dude.
